'''''Rathnagiri Rahasya''''' ({{lang-kn|ರತ್ನಗಿರಿ ರಹಸ್ಯ}}) is a 1957 [[Kannada language]] [[Mystery film|mystery]] – [[Adventure film|adventure]] – [[fantasy film]], directed and produced by [[B. R. Panthulu]], starring [[Udaykumar]] and [[Jamuna (actress)|Jamuna]] in the lead roles.<ref>[http://paaru.in/movies/rathnagiri-rahasya-kannada-1905 Rathnagiri Rahasya-1905-Kannada Movie Information]</ref> The film was made simultaneously in [[Tamil language]] as ''[[Thangamalai Ragasiyam]]'',<ref>[[Thangamalai Ragasiyam]]</ref>{{Circular reference|date=October 2015}}  released in the same year, with [[Sivaji Ganesan]] in the lead, along with Jamuna reprising her role. Most of the technical crew remained the same for both Tamil and Kannada versions. It was also dubbed into Telugu as ''Rathnagiri Rahasyam'' and dubbed in Hindi as ''Suhaag''. Future acclaimed director [[Puttanna Kanagal]] made his debut as an assistant director in this film.<ref>[http://shopping.chitraloka.com/history/3872-history-48-puttanna-kanagal-becomes-independent-director.html History 48 – Puttanna Kanagal Becomes Independent Director]</ref> This film screened at IFFI 1992 B. R. Panthalu Homage section. Video clips of some songs in this film such as ''Kalyana Namma'', ''Oh Raja Maharaja'' and more were shot in [[Gevacolor]].

== Plot ==
Udaykumar plays the role of a prince who is separated from his parents by his father's foe at a very young age. He grew up as a ferocious and vicious caveman. Then he meets Jamuna, who by her word of love and affection turns him for good. Both set out to find the secret of Rathnagiri to find and save Udaykumar's parents.

